{"article_id":"cGEpUUfknGmXzX7I","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Self-made billionaire Ross Perot ,","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"who ran for president in 1992 and 1996 ,","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"has died at age 89 after a five-month battle with leukemia ,","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"the Dallas Morning News reported .","depth":4},{"id":4,"text":"Perot ,","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"who won19 percent of the vote as a third-party candidate in 1992 ,","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"died early Tuesday at his home in Dallas","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"surrounded by his family ,","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"family spokesman James Fuller said .","depth":4},{"id":9,"text":"The native-born Texan ,","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"who made his billions","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"by founding Electronic Data Systems Corp. ,","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"was seen by admirers as a patriot","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"who served his country well before his two failed bids for the White House .","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"In 1979 , he financed a private commando raid","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"to free two EDS employees","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"being held in a prison in Iran .","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"He was also a tireless advocate for Vietnam veterans .","depth":4},{"id":18,"text":"In 1992 , Perot spent more than $ 60 million of his own money","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"to run against incumbent President George H.W . Bush and challenger Bill Clinton ,","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"promising to bring his business acumen to the nation 's finances .","depth":6},{"id":21,"text":"Some Republicans blamed him for Bush 's loss ,","depth":6},{"id":22,"text":"noting","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"he pulled the largest percentage of votes for a third-party candidate since former President Theodore Roosevelt 's 1912 bid .","depth":7},{"id":24,"text":"Perot 's second campaign four years later fizzled ,","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"as he gathered just 8 percent of the vote ,","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"and the Reform Party","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"that he founded","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"and hoped to build into a national political force","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"began to fall apart .","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"However , Perot 's ideas on trade and deficit reduction remained part of the political landscape .","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"He blamed both major parties for running up a huge federal budget deficit","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"and letting American jobs to be sent to other countries .","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"The movement of U.S. jobs to Mexico ,","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"he said ,","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"created a `` giant sucking sound . ''","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"Perot continued to speak out about federal spending for many years .","depth":6},{"id":37,"text":"In 2008 , he launched a website","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"to highlight the nation 's debt with a ticker","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"that tracked the rising total ,","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"a blog and a chart presentation .","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"Henry Ross Perot was born in Texarkana on June 27 , 1930 .","depth":3},{"id":42,"text":"His father was a cotton broker ;","depth":5},{"id":43,"text":"his mother a secretary .","depth":5},{"id":44,"text":"Perot said","depth":5},{"id":45,"text":"his family survived the Depression relatively well through hard work and by managing their money carefully .","depth":5},{"id":46,"text":"Young Perot 's first job was delivering papers in a poor , mostly black part of town from his pony , Miss Bee .","depth":4},{"id":47,"text":"Perot said","depth":6},{"id":48,"text":"when the newspaper tried to cut his commission ,","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"he complained to the publisher","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"- and won .","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"He said","depth":6},{"id":52,"text":"he learned to take problems straight to the top .","depth":6},{"id":53,"text":"From Texarkana , Perot went to the U.S . Naval Academy","depth":5},{"id":54,"text":"even though he had never been on a ship","depth":6},{"id":55,"text":"or seen the ocean .","depth":6},{"id":56,"text":"After the Navy , Perot joined International Business Machines in 1955","depth":7},{"id":57,"text":"and quickly became a top salesman .","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"In his last year at IBM , he filled his sales quota for the year in January .","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"In 1962 , with $ 1,000 from his wife , Margot , Perot founded Electronic Data Systems .","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"Hardware accounted for about 80 % of the computer business ,","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"Perot said ,","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"and IBM was n't interested in the other 20 % ,","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"including services .","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"Many of the early hires at EDS were former military men ,","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"and they had to abide by Perot 's strict dress code","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"- white shirts , ties , no beards or mustaches -","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"and long work days .","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"Many had crew cuts , like Perot .","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"The company 's big break came in the mid-1960s","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"when the federal government created Medicare and Medicaid , the health programs for seniors , the disabled and the poor .","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"States needed help","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"in running the programs ,","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"and EDS won contracts","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"- starting in Texas -","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"to handle the millions of claims .","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"EDS first sold stock to the public in 1968 ,","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"and overnight , Perot was worth $ 350 million .","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"His fortune doubled","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"and tripled","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"as the stock price rose steadily .","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"In 1984 , he sold control of the company to General Motors Corp. for $ 2.5 billion","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"and received $ 700 million in a buyout .","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"In 2008 , EDS was sold to Hewlett-Packard Co .","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"Perot went on to establish another computer-services company , Perot Systems Corp .","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"He retired as CEO in 2000","depth":13},{"id":86,"text":"and was succeeded by his son , Ross Perot Jr .","depth":13},{"id":87,"text":"In 2009 , Dell Inc. bought Perot Systems .","depth":12},{"id":88,"text":"In September 2011 , Forbes magazine estimated Perot 's wealth at $ 3.5 billion","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"and ranked him No . 91 on its list of richest Americans .","depth":12}],"relations":[{"parent":179,"left":130,"right":178,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":130,"left":98,"right":129,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":98,"left":93,"right":97,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":93,"left":92,"right":3,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":92,"left":91,"right":2,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":91,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":97,"left":96,"right":8,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":96,"left":94,"right":95,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":94,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":95,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":129,"left":106,"right":128,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":106,"left":105,"right":17,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":105,"left":102,"right":104,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":102,"left":100,"right":101,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":100,"left":9,"right":99,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":99,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":101,"left":12,"right":13,"r